## A. Partial gating (most likely source of random 503/errors)

### A1. `v2LiveGuard` covers 12 of 163 mutating routes (~7%)
- **Verified**: `total_mutating=163 gated=12 ungated=151`.
- **Gated**: `comments/route.js`, `comments/[id]/{vote,report,context-tag}/route.js`,
  `bookmarks/route.js`, `notifications/route.js`, `quiz/{start,submit}/route.js`,
  `expert/ask/route.js`, `recap/[id]/submit/route.js`, `stories/read/route.js`,
  `ads/{impression,serve}/route.js`.
- **Not gated**: every `admin/*`, `stripe/*`, `billing/*`, `auth/*`, `kids/*`,
  `messages/*`, `follows/*`, `family/*`, `expert-sessions/*`, `reports/*`, `push/*`,
  `promo/*`, `support/*`, `access-request/*`, `ios/*`, `cron/*`.
- **Effect when `v2_live=false`**: comments/quiz return 503; admin + billing + messages
  keep working. A half-honored master switch creates exactly the "errors in some places,
  fine in others" pattern.
- **Risk tier**: architectural.

### A2. Client vs. server gate mismatch (comments)
- **Client** (`CommentComposer.tsx:47`): `hasPermission('comments.post')` â€” a global perm.
- **Server** (`schema/023_phase15_mute_checks.sql:93-131`):
  - `email_verified` check
  - mute/ban check (`_user_is_comment_blocked`)
  - **per-article quiz pass** (`user_passed_article_quiz`)
  - length + depth checks
- Per-article quiz state is NOT representable in the global perm cache.
- **Result**: composer renders, server returns 400 with generic `"Could not post comment"`.
- Same shape applies to reply/vote/tag/report paths.

### A3. Feature-flag cache is per-process, 10s TTL, no cross-instance invalidation
- `lib/featureFlags.js:11-12`, `TTL_MS = 10_000`.
- Admin flips a flag â†’ instance A picks it up in 0s, instance B in up to 10s.
- During the window, requests landing on stale instances behave differently.
- Symptom: "I retried and it worked this time."

