## S. Cron surface audit

Scope: `api/cron/**` (10 routes).

**Overall posture: solid.** Auth clean, COPPA/GDPR paths safe, observability thorough. Two real issues.

### S.1 `send-emails` lacks atomic claim â€” double-send risk

`send-emails/route.js:53-59` reads `notifications WHERE email_sent=false LIMIT 50`, then updates row-by-row. **Two overlapping cron runs read and process the same batch.** Drifts from the send-push L19 fix (`98c6662`, schema/159) which added `claim_push_batch()` RPC with `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` + 5-min stale-claim reclaim.

