## W. Kids iOS app audit

Scope: `VerityPostKids/VerityPostKids/**` â€” pair-code auth, JWT handling, reader/quiz flow, parental gate, celebration scenes.

**Overall posture: mixed.** Auth and JWT surface has **serious COPPA/security gaps**. Reader/quiz surface is mostly clean. Parental gate has a **Critical Apple Kids Category review risk** (defined but barely wired) plus one concrete feature bug.

### W.1 Keychain persistence across app uninstall â€” critical shared-device risk

- `PairingClient.swift:274-307` stores JWT in iOS Keychain with `kSecAttrAccessibleWhenUnlockedThisDeviceOnly`.
- **iOS Keychain is NOT automatically cleared on app uninstall.** Reinstalling the app restores the previous kid's JWT without requiring a new pair-code.
- Family shared-iPad scenario: parent uninstalls â†’ reinstalls â†’ old kid's session silently resumes.
- No install-scoped key or freshness check before `KidsAuth.restore()` (`KidsAuth.swift:27`).

### W.2 7-day JWT lifetime â€” aggressive for COPPA

- `api/kids/pair/route.js:24` mints JWT with 7-day TTL.
- Stolen iPad â†’ 7-day impersonation window for the kid's identity (reads, quizzes, streaks).
- No refresh-token rotation, no device binding, no biometric re-auth.
- Industry norm: short-lived (1h) access token + refresh token bound to original device.

### W.3 Multi-device pairing + no per-device revocation

- JWTs are not device-bound. A single `kid_profile_id` can have multiple live JWTs across devices.
- If one device is lost, parent cannot revoke just that device's token â€” must regenerate pair code (which doesn't invalidate *existing* JWTs, only future pairings).
- Combined with W.2, a compromised device holds a valid identity for up to 7 days regardless of parental action.

### W.4 No session revocation on parent-initiated changes

- Parent removes a kid â†’ DB flags `is_active=false` or deletes profile. Refresh is blocked (`api/kids/refresh/route.js:93`).
- **Existing JWTs remain valid until their own `exp`.** Kid can keep using the app for up to 7 days post-removal.
- Parent-initiated pause has the same lag.
- No instant invalidation path exists.

### W.5 Pair-code length mismatch between iOS and server

- `PairCodeView.swift:133-139` enforces exactly 8 characters.
- `api/kids/pair/route.js:52` accepts 6-16 characters.
- If a parent generates a 6-char or 10-char code (via admin tooling or a future change), the iOS input silently rejects without telling the parent why.

### W.6 KidsAppState doesn't re-sync on foreground

- `KidsAppState.swift` (`@Published` properties) loads on `.task(id: auth.kid?.id)` at `KidsAppRoot.swift:54`.
- `scenePhase.active` hook at `KidsAppRoot.swift:67` refreshes JWT but NOT kid state.
- Parent changes `max_daily_minutes` / streak reset / pause on web â†’ child sees stale cached values until app restart.
- Matches the J.4 adult iOS gap (perms don't refresh on foreground) â€” same class of bug, more urgent here because the parent controls are the safety surface.

### W.7 ParentalGateModal has near-zero callers â€” **Apple review risk**

`ParentalGateModal.swift` is fully implemented (lines 3-246) but only wired to **three callsites**:
- `ProfileView.swift` â€” Unpair, Legal links
- `PairCodeView.swift` â€” Help email

**Missing ParentalGate on:**
- External links anywhere in article content (reader itself has no outbound nav â€” OK â€” but any future feature that adds links needs this)
- Any in-app purchase / account-linking flow
- Settings that could affect the child's data

CLAUDE.md documents the intended usage (external links, IAP, settings); the intended callers don't exist. **Apple Kids Category review expects ParentalGate on all sensitive operations.** Ship-blocker unless scope is explicitly documented as "kid app has no such surfaces."

### W.8 Day-3 streak milestone is missing â€” feature bug

`KidsAppState.swift:49-56` hardcodes the milestone switch:
```swift
case 7:  return milestone
case 14: return milestone
case 30: return milestone
```

**CLAUDE.md specifies milestones at 3 / 7 / 14 / 30 days.** The Day-3 celebration never fires. A kid who hits day 3 of their first streak gets no badge; the first celebration moment lands on day 7 â€” a week of reading with no visible progress. Feature parity bug.

### W.9 Math challenge is kid-solvable

- `ParentalGateModal.swift:26-27, 195-197`: random numbers 4-15, addition only. Sum range 8-30.
- Clever 7-year-old can brute-force or reverse-engineer after a few attempts.
- Lockout after 3 failures helps, but a persistent kid can retry after 5 min.
- Consider harder operations (two-digit multiplication) for real parental intent.

### W.10 Parental-gate lockout is device-local

- Lockout state in UserDefaults (`ParentalGateModal.swift:37`). No server-side enforcement.
- Reinstall or device reset â†’ lockout cleared.
- No concurrent-attempt guard: if two views call `.parentalGate` simultaneously, only one modal appears; the other request is silently lost.

### W.11 Scene queue races on category tap

- Scene queue serializes streak + badge celebrations correctly (`KidsAppRoot.swift:195-222`).
- **But**: `present(_:)` at line 171 directly sets `activeSheet`, **overwriting the scene queue.** If a kid taps a category mid-celebration, the next celebration is discarded.
- K6 fix (cancel GreetingScene on disappear + name change) is verified present at `GreetingScene.swift:108-120`.

### W.12 Quiz pass threshold hardcoded at 60%

- `KidQuizEngineView.swift:337`: `ceil(total * 0.6)`.
- Not DB-sourced. Per-article threshold adjustment requires a code release.
- Matches the wider pattern in the codebase: per-feature constants live in code, not `settings` table.

### W.13 Accessibility gaps on celebration scenes

VoiceOver labels missing from:
- `StreakScene.swift` â€” no labels on flame icon, streak number, milestone card, buttons
- `BadgeUnlockScene.swift` â€” no labels on badge, text, buttons
- `QuizPassScene.swift` â€” no labels on progress dots, answer chips, result ring

`GreetingScene` has labels (lines 93-94). The inconsistency means a VoiceOver user reading with their kid hears the greeting but nothing when the badge unlocks.

Decorative particle emitters should be `.accessibilityHidden(true)` â€” not explicitly marked.

### W.14 Reduced-motion not respected in reader/quiz

- `KidQuizEngineView.swift:282` uses `.withAnimation(K.springSnap)` unconditionally.
