## AA. Access / onboarding audit

Scope: `/login`, `/signup`, `/signup/pick-username`, `/welcome`, `/verify-email`, access codes, age gate.

### AA.1 Access-code gate is NOT enforced on signup

- `access_codes` table exists in schema; admin UI at `/admin/access/page.tsx` manages codes.
- **Neither `/api/auth/signup` nor `api/auth/callback` (OAuth) checks the table** or decrements usage.
- Pre-launch invite gating is a fiction today â€” any email or OAuth can sign up regardless of code.
- Rate limits + email enumeration defense are in place; but the "only people with a code get in" promise isn't.

### AA.2 Verify-email token has no session-match check

- If user A is logged in as `alice@example.com` and pastes a verify link for `bob@example.com`, Supabase verifies bob's email flag under alice's session.
- Supabase token single-use protection mitigates replay risk; the cross-session UX can wedge state.
