## BB. Ads / sponsors audit

Scope: `api/ads/*`, `api/admin/ad-{placements,campaigns}/*`, `components/Ad.jsx`, `schema/110_adsense_adapter.sql`.

### BB.1 `serve_ad` RPC has no kids-account check â€” COPPA risk

- `schema/110_adsense_adapter.sql:31` â€” `serve_ad` reads `users.plan_id` + `users.stripe_customer_id` to gate paid-tier ad-free, but **doesn't check `users.is_kids_account` or any kid-profile flag**.
- A free-tier kid-account today sees no ads because the VerityPostKids iOS app doesn't mount `<Ad>`.
- Any future web kid surface, or a kid using a parent's shared browser with kid-profile toggling, would light this up. **COPPA violation** when it happens.
- Defense-in-depth missing â€” client gate is the only thing stopping kids from seeing ads.

### BB.2 Campaign budgets are not enforced

- `log_ad_impression` RPC (`schema/110:137`) does `UPDATE ad_campaigns SET spent_cents = spent_cents + v_revenue` â€” no cap check.
- `ad_campaigns.total_budget_cents` and `daily_budget_cents` are persisted but not consulted during impression logging.
- Campaigns overrun their budgets indefinitely. Direct revenue leak if ads are priced at CPM and an advertiser hits their cap.
- No alert when a campaign crosses budget. Admin must eyeball `spent_cents vs total_budget_cents` in the dashboard.

### BB.3 Ad creative URLs / HTML aren't server-validated

- `creative_url`, `click_url`, `creative_html` stored as-is from admin POST.
- Client-side allowlist in `Ad.jsx:86-90` rejects `javascript:` / `data:` on render.
- **Single line of defense.** A rogue admin (or compromised admin account) injects `<script>` via `creative_html` â†’ XSS on every reader who sees that slot.
- Content-Security-Policy might help but admin-injected HTML often bypasses CSP by design.

### BB.4 Fill-rate telemetry is dark

- Event types defined in code: `ads_filtered_cap`, `ads_filtered_bot`, `ads_unfilled`.
- `serve_ad` RPC **never emits them.** Admin has zero visibility into why serves failed or what the fill rate looks like.
- Admin analytics can't distinguish "no ad served because cap" from "no ad served because no campaigns."

### BB.5 Tier-suppression race on mid-session downgrade

- User downgrades from paid-active to free mid-session. Server has the new tier, but the current page may have a cached ad response that already rendered.
- User sees one more ad they shouldn't. Narrow window; narrow harm.

### BB.6 Impression dedup missing

- `log_ad_impression` inserts per-call, no `UNIQUE(slot_id, user_id, article_id, served_at::date)` constraint.
- Same ad appearing in two slots on one page logs two impressions â€” double-counts revenue.

### BB.7 Frequency cap race

- Two concurrent `serve_ad` calls (parallel requests for two slots on same page) both read "count below cap," both serve, impression cap overshoots by one.

### BB.8 No conversion attribution

- Clicks recorded, spend recorded, **no UTM / referrer / conversion linkage.**
- Admin sees cost-per-click but not downstream conversion. Advertisers can't evaluate ROI; platform can't tune pricing.

### BB.9 What's clean

- Sponsors are a separate content type via `articles.sponsor_id`, not an ad variant â€” surface correctly separated.
- Admin permission gating on ads/campaigns/sponsors is consistent with the broader admin pattern.
- `Ad.jsx` client URL allowlist is real (belt-and-suspenders if admin POST validation gets added).

