## GG. Supabase RLS policy audit

Scope: `schema/reset_and_rebuild_v2.sql` + numbered migrations touching `CREATE POLICY`, `ALTER POLICY`, `DROP POLICY`, `is_kid_delegated()`, `auth.uid()` usage.

### GG.1 CRITICAL â€” `follows_select` has a world-open `OR true` clause

- `schema/reset_and_rebuild_v2.sql:3828`:
```sql
CREATE POLICY "follows_select" ON "follows" FOR SELECT USING (
  follower_id = auth.uid() OR following_id = auth.uid() OR true
);
```
- **Anon and every authenticated user can read the entire follows graph.**
- Who follows whom globally is an open social-graph export.
- The `OR true` at the end is either intentional (social transparency) or drift from a more restrictive intent. The remainder of the policy suggests it was meant to be per-user.
- **Ship-blocker if unintentional**; if intentional, should be explicit (drop the two per-user clauses entirely and comment "follows graph is public by design").

### GG.2 HIGH â€” Kid-JWT SELECT gap on quiz_attempts

- Base policy `quiz_attempts_select` (line 3638): `user_id = auth.uid() OR is_admin_or_above()`. No kid-JWT branch.
- Migration 132 added `quiz_attempts_insert_kid_jwt` with `is_kid_delegated() AND kid_profile_id = auth.uid()` â€” but only for INSERT.
- **Likely bug**: kids can write quiz attempts but can't read their own back. Kid-facing quiz history / streak recap would 0-fill.
- Needs a `quiz_attempts_select_kid_jwt` permissive policy to match.

### GG.3 MEDIUM â€” Permission architecture is world-readable

- `permission_set_perms_select` (line 4827): `FOR SELECT USING (true)`.
- `role_permission_sets_select` (line 4828): same.
- `plan_permission_sets_select` (line 4829): same.
- Anon and any user can enumerate the entire permission-to-role + permission-to-plan mapping.
- Doesn't leak user-specific grants, but exposes the mechanism. An attacker probing for privilege-escalation can map which perms unlock what; speeds up targeted attacks.

### GG.4 MEDIUM â€” `audit_log_insert` has open INSERT

