## KK. Feeds / RSS ingest audit

Scope: `api/admin/feeds/**`, `api/newsroom/ingest/run/route.ts`, `/admin/feeds/page.tsx`, `/admin/newsroom/page.tsx`, `lib/pipeline/scrape-article.ts`, schema `feeds` + `discovery_items` + `rss_feeds` legacy.

**Separation from U (AI pipeline)**: U covered generate/cluster/persist (downstream of clusters). KK covers the upstream path â€” how raw articles enter the system before clustering.

### KK.1 Feed URLs aren't validated on insert (critical)

- `POST /api/admin/feeds` accepts any URL.
- No DNS lookup, no HTTP HEAD, no SSL cert check, no content-type verification pre-insert.
- A compromised admin (or a social-engineering sweep of multiple admins) can inject arbitrary URLs into the ingest pool, polluting clusters and propagating malicious content downstream.
- `feeds.created_by` column exists but is **never populated** by the POST route â€” no provenance trail on who added each feed.

### KK.2 No credibility scoring (high)

- `feeds` schema has zero columns for `credibility_score` / `trust_level` / `verified_by` / `ranking`.
- Reuters feed and a fringe blog contribute with identical weight.
- Profile settings has a "Hide low-credibility sources" toggle â€” surfacing data that doesn't exist.
- AI generation downstream gets no source-level trust signal; can't bias prompts or safety checks.

### KK.3 No automatic cron pull (high)

- Ingest only runs when an admin clicks "Refresh feeds" in the newsroom UI (`admin/newsroom/page.tsx:16`).
- Manual rate limit: 5 runs per 600s.
- **Weekend / admin-offline coverage**: zero new content enters the system until someone pushes the button.
- Compounds with KK.8 (no auto-pause): dead feeds keep getting polled manually forever; new content only enters manually.

### KK.4 Audience filtering was dropped in the unified-feed pivot (high)

- `ingest/run/route.ts:187-196`: queries `feeds` by `is_active + feed_type IN ('feed','rss')` only.
- `feeds.audience` column still exists in schema but is **ignored during ingest**.
- Clusters default to `audience='adult'` (line 431); operator picks audience at generation time.
- If the AI generator misclassifies or fails the audience gate, kid-unsafe source material could feed into the kid pool.
- Defense-in-depth at ingest level is gone; relies entirely on downstream correctness.

### KK.5 No URL canonicalization on dedup (medium)

- `ingest/run/route.ts:234-275`: dedup is `existingUrls.has(it.raw_url)` â€” exact string match.
- `utm_*`, `fbclid`, `gclid` tracking params **NOT stripped**.
- Case **not normalized** (`Example.com` vs `example.com`).
- Fragments **not stripped** (`/article` vs `/article#main`).
- Redirect variants + syndicated URLs with tracking params all create duplicate `discovery_items`.
- Cluster pool pollution; compute wasted on dedupe of near-duplicates.

### KK.6 rss-parser has no XXE hardening (medium)

- `ingest/run/route.ts:92-95`: `new Parser({ timeout: 5000, headers: {...} })` â€” no explicit XML-entity-resolution options.
- A malicious RSS feed with `<!DOCTYPE foo [<!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "file:///etc/passwd">]>` could leak server files depending on rss-parser's XML backend defaults.
- Comment at head of the file: "ported verbatim from snapshot" â€” suggests this code wasn't audited for security post-port.
- Combined with KK.1 (any URL goes): attacker with admin can add a hostile feed.

### KK.7 No robots.txt check (medium, dup of U.4)

- Confirmed at the ingest layer too â€” no robots check before fetching.
- User-Agent `VerityPost/1.0` identifies us; target sites see us but we ignore their exclusion rules.
- ToS / CFAA / IP-ban exposure.

### KK.8 Feed failures aren't written to the row (medium)

- `feeds.error_count` / `last_error` / `last_error_at` columns exist.
- `ingest/run/route.ts:212-231`: failures counted in the run summary only; **feed row never updated**.
- Admin "Re-pull" action manually resets `error_count=0`, but no other code path increments it.
- A consistently failing feed has no visible failure history on its row.
- Admin UI `deriveStatus()` at `feeds/page.tsx:104-111` computes "broken" from `error_count >= brokenFailCount` â€” but the counter doesn't get incremented, so status never flips.

### KK.9 No auto-pause for stale / broken feeds (medium)

- `deriveStatus()` is derived at render time, not persisted.
- Feeds with `is_active=true` keep getting polled regardless of derived status.
- Dead feeds waste fetch budget forever until an admin notices and manually pauses.

### KK.10 Slow feeds starve parallel fetches (medium)

- `Promise.allSettled` on all feeds with shared 6s timeout.
- One slow feed at 5.9s per item eats the window; parallel fetches of other feeds don't get their fair share.
- No per-feed budget; no staggered execution.

### KK.11 Ingest has no per-run item cap (medium)

- Rate limit gates runs (5 per 10min), not items per run.
- Batch insertion at 500/batch with no upper bound.
- A compromised feed flooding thousands of items in one run could overload clustering.

### KK.12 HTML scrape relies on Cheerio, not a sanitizer (low)

- `scrape-article.ts:79-118` removes `script, style, nav, footer, header, aside, iframe, noscript, .ad, ...` via Cheerio selectors.
- **Cheerio removal is not a security boundary.** Missed selectors or inline event handlers on allowed tags can slip through.
- Raw body set to `null` during ingest (deferred to AI layer), mitigating immediate render risk â€” but text still flows to AI and downstream.
- No DOMPurify / sanitize-html in the chain.

### KK.13 Admin add / toggle / delete are audit-logged (clean)

- `recordAdminAction` fires on all three.
- Minor footgun: `POST /api/admin/feeds` defaults `is_active` to `true` when omitted (line 55). A front-end bug that omits the field accidentally enables a feed meant to be paused.

### KK.14 Legacy schema drift resolved (clean)

- `rss_feeds` â†’ `feeds` rename migration is clean.
- Only residual comment at `admin/feeds/page.tsx:26-28` documents the column rename (outletâ†’name/source_name, activeâ†’is_active, fail_countâ†’error_count, last_pullâ†’last_polled_at).
- No active code references to the legacy table name.

### KK.15 No drift markers

No `TODO` / `FIXME` / `HACK` in the ingest surface.

