## PP. Performance + Core Web Vitals audit

Scope: bundle composition hints, image optimization, font loading, client/server split, list rendering, cache headers, Sentry weight.

### PP.1 Zero code splitting on 5K+ line pages (critical)

- `profile/settings/page.tsx` is **5,174 LOC** (actual; earlier referred to as 3,800 â€” it grew).
- `profile/page.tsx` is 1,714 LOC.
- `admin/newsroom/page.tsx` is 2,349 LOC.
- **No `dynamic(() => import(...))` anywhere in the codebase.** All large pages are single client bundles.
- Settings loads ~5KB+ of JS before interactivity. No route-level split, no modal/drawer split.

### PP.2 Everything is a client component (critical)

- **112 `'use client'` directives; zero `'use server'`.**
- Every page does data fetching in `useEffect` + `useState`.
- LCP pays the full round-trip: JS bundle â†’ React hydrate â†’ Supabase client init â†’ first query â†’ render.
- RSC / server components would allow direct DB queries server-side, smaller JS payloads, server-rendered markup for SEO.
- Current architecture forces all fetching client-side.

### PP.3 Zero virtualization on long admin lists (critical)

- No `react-window` / `react-virtual` anywhere.
- `/admin/users/page.tsx` (897 LOC) â€” `DataTable` pagination, but no virt inside rows.
- `/admin/newsroom/page.tsx` (2,349 LOC) â€” cluster list + per-row detail rendered.
- `/bookmarks/page.tsx` (617 LOC) â€” unknown list size.
- `/browse/page.tsx` (518 LOC) â€” categories + article cards per category, unbounded.
- Admin pages with 100+ rows render all DOM nodes. Main-thread jank for staff.

### PP.4 Zero image lazy loading (critical)

- No `loading="lazy"` attributes anywhere.
- No IntersectionObserver patterns.
- All images (wherever they exist) load eagerly on route.
- Combined with PP.5 (no `next/image`), images pay full cost upfront regardless of viewport position.

### PP.5 No `next/image` usage (medium)

- No `next/image` imports detected.
- User-uploaded content paths (article hero, banner, avatar URLs) render via CSS `background-image` or raw `<img>` tags (though `<img>` tags are rare â€” most avatars are CSS-styled div initials).
- No AVIF support, no responsive `srcset`, no automatic dimension attributes.
- CLS risk on any image-containing page.

### PP.6 No API route cache-control headers (medium)

- Zero `Cache-Control` headers set by API routes.
- Static-ish public data (`/api/categories`, `/api/plans`) re-fetched on every request.
- CDN caching opportunities missed.
- Also: no explicit `no-store` on sensitive routes â€” relies on default browser behavior.

### PP.7 Overfetching via `select('*')` (medium)

- 20+ queries with `select('*')`:
  - `admin/permissions/page.tsx`: 7 of them (permissions, permission_sets, permission_set_perms, roles, plans, role_permission_sets, plan_permission_sets).
  - `admin/plans/page.tsx`, `admin/categories/page.tsx` each use `select('*')`.
- Unused columns dropped at render, but network + JSON parse cost paid.
- On pages with heavy joins, this adds up.

### PP.8 Supabase client recreated per-component (medium)

- `const supabase = createClient()` called inside component bodies across many files (CommentThread, profile, story, browse, CommentComposer).
- No React Query / SWR / custom cache.
- Potential re-render leaks: Settings page's 5K LOC is likely to re-render sub-sections on form input; if `createClient()` isn't memoized or if hooks re-fire queries on each render, that's query-per-keystroke territory.

### PP.9 Skeleton loaders lack height guards (medium)

- `SkeletonBar` / `SkeletonRow` imported in profile pages.
- Used with explicit `width` but no `height` on the parent container.
- Skeleton typically single-line (~20px), real content multi-line (~60px). Swap causes visible layout shift.

### PP.10 Sentry always bundled (medium)

- ~40KB Sentry browser SDK loaded on every authenticated page via `sentry.client.config.js:16`.
- Not lazy-loaded â€” initialized immediately when DSN is present.
- `tracesSampleRate: 0` â€” tracing disabled, SDK still in bundle.
- Non-production branches skip via env var, but prod always ships it.

### PP.11 Real-time channel leak risk (already flagged, low)

- `CommentThread.tsx:191` channel name: `article-comments:${articleId}:${Date.now()}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 8)}`.
- Cleanup on unmount exists (line 259). Rapid tab-switching could briefly stack channels before cleanup.
- Anti-pattern; fixed channel name per article would be cleaner.

### PP.12 What's clean

- **`next/font`** with `display: 'swap'` + CSS variables. Self-hosted, no `@import url()` render-blocking.
- **Third-party scripts use `strategy="afterInteractive"`** (GA4, AdSense).
- **Parallel fetches used correctly** where present: Home `Promise.all([stories, breaking, categories])`, admin/permissions 7-way parallel, admin/newsroom 2-way.
- **No `react-icons` / `lucide-react` / `moment` / `date-fns` / `dayjs`** â€” zero bloat from icon/date libs. Icons are inline SVG; date logic is hand-rolled (`timeAgo()` in `browse/page.tsx:80-87`).
- **Root layouts are server components** â€” `admin/layout.tsx` + `app/layout.js`. No monolithic client tree at layout level.

