## RR. Observability + error-handling audit

Scope: `lib/cronLog.js`, `lib/cronHeartbeat.js`, `lib/apiErrors.js`, `lib/observability.js`, `sentry.client.config.js`, `sentry.shared.js`, `/api/errors/route.js`, error boundaries, iOS crash reporting.

### RR.1 API routes barely emit to Sentry (critical)

- **~3 of 216 API routes** call `Sentry.captureException` or use the `safeErrorResponse()` helper that bridges to Sentry.
- The rest log via `console.error('[tag]', err)` which lands in Vercel function logs but **not Sentry**.
- No aggregation, no alerting, no trend analysis on 98%+ of server error paths.
- Concretely: `api/follows`, `api/bookmarks`, `api/supervisor/opt-in`, `api/supervisor/opt-out` â€” all have console.error + manual generic response, no Sentry bridge.

### RR.2 No server-side Sentry config file (high)

- Only `sentry.client.config.js` exists.
- **Missing**: `sentry.server.config.js`, `sentry.edge.config.js`.
- `lib/observability.js:19-24` checks `SENTRY_DSN` / `NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN` â€” if neither, falls back to `console.error` in dev.
- Prod relies on `@sentry/nextjs` auto-init via env vars, not the recommended explicit config pattern. Server exceptions caught by Next.js may not reach Sentry consistently.

### RR.3 iOS is completely dark on crashes (critical)

- **No Sentry-Swift, no Firebase Crashlytics, no crash reporter at all.**
- `VerityPost/VerityPost/Log.swift` is a debug-only shim â€” release builds compile to no-ops.
- `BlockService.swift`, report services, etc. emit `Log.d(...)` but no remote observability.
- App crashes invisible to operators unless users file support tickets.
- iOS testing and launch will fly blind on stability.

### RR.4 No alerting / operator wakeup anywhere (high)

- No Slack webhook, PagerDuty, on-call integration in code.
- `withCronLog` writes to `webhook_log` but nothing reads it for alert purposes.
- Failure modes that leave no signal:
  - Cron doesn't fire at all (no start heartbeat to check).
  - Rate-limiter bootstrap fails (console.error only).
  - Stripe signature validation fails (logged, not alerted).
  - `webhook_log` DB is full or unavailable â€” cron continues silently.
- Manual log-scanning is the only path to incident detection.

### RR.5 `/profile/error.js` boundary is silent (medium)

- Root error boundary (`/app/error.js`) + story boundary (`/app/story/[slug]/error.js`) both POST to `/api/errors`.
- **`/profile/error.js` doesn't.** Renders "couldn't load" without reporting. Silent failure on the 1700-line profile page.

### RR.6 `/api/errors` has no dedup (medium)

- Accepts POST, rate-limited 60/min per IP.
- **No fingerprint dedup.** A bug hitting 1000 users creates 1000 rows.
- **No Sentry bridge either** â€” the endpoint writes to its own local table; doesn't forward to Sentry for aggregation.
- Storage grows linearly with error volume; no alerting.

### RR.7 Drift between `apiErrors.js` and actual route usage (medium)

- `apiErrors.js` exists and maps Postgres error codes to generic messages â€” solid helper.
- Only ~3 routes import it (primary user: `/api/cron/process-deletions`).
- Most routes hand-roll try/catch with inline `NextResponse.json({ error: '...' }, { status: 400 })` and miss the Sentry bridge the helper provides.
- Helper is good; adoption is nearly zero.

### RR.8 PostgreSQL `RAISE EXCEPTION` messages pass through to clients (low)

- Triggers can include free-text messages (`P0001`).
- `apiErrors.js` sanitizes: 240-char cap + whitespace collapse.
- Still: a trigger author who embeds user data or credentials in a RAISE message leaks to the client.
- Not a current leak; latent risk.

### RR.9 Untagged logs in library functions (low)

- `lib/scoring.js`, `lib/featureFlags.js` emit `console.error` without `[module.name]` tag.
- Hard to grep in Vercel logs; breaks the tagged-search convention used elsewhere.

### RR.10 Zero test coverage (high; infrastructure crossover)

- No `.test.ts` / `.test.js` / `.spec.ts` files anywhere.
- Observability wiring assumes production behavior; no unit tests verify error-path shapes, Sentry calls, or cron heartbeat emission.

### RR.11 What's clean

- **Cron observability is genuinely excellent.** `withCronLog` applied on all 10 cron routes â€” start/end/error phases to `webhook_log`, Sentry bridge on catch, fail-safe on `webhook_log` insert failure.
- **`logCronHeartbeat`** dual-layer phase tracking (start/error/end) correctly emitted.
- **Sentry PII scrubbing** is comprehensive (`sentry.shared.js`): emails, Authorization headers, bearer tokens, stripe-signature, PINs stripped via `beforeSend`.
- **`truncateIpV4`** applied on `/api/errors` (GDPR-lean).
- **User-agent** truncated to 1KB to prevent log-inflation attacks.
- **Tagging convention**: `[cron:name]`, `[api.error]`, `[cron.heartbeat]` â€” greppable across Vercel logs when present.

